{
  "texts": [
    "This instability makes sustained, reliable public health monitoring based solely on these sources precarious and underscores the need for researchers and public health agencies to consider data source diversification and contingency planning.",
    "Furthermore, algorithmic bias presents a significant risk to the validity and fairness of sentiment analysis findings (11, 65).",
    "All sentiment analysis models, from traditional machine learning to LLMs, can inherit and even amplify biases present in their training data or underlying lexicons (46, 65).",
    "For instance, LLMs have shown susceptibility to biases related to cultural contexts or linguistic framing (38, 54).",
    "Such biases can lead to skewed insights and potentially inequitable public health outcomes."
  ]
}